# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CUSTOMERS - LIST AND LOOKUP
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

@AutoService_ApiService_HostAddress = {{$processEnv AutoService_ApiService_HostAddress}}
@AdminEmail = {{$processEnv ARSM_TEST_ADMIN_EMAIL}}
@AdminPassword = {{$processEnv ARSM_TEST_ADMIN_PASSWORD}}
@NonAdminEmail = {{$processEnv ARSM_TEST_MECHANIC_EMAIL}}
@NonAdminPassword = {{$processEnv ARSM_TEST_MECHANIC_PASSWORD}}
@KnownCustomerEmail = {{$processEnv ARSM_TEST_CUSTOMER_EMAIL}}
@RunId = {{$timestamp}}
@SeedCustomerId = 1
@NonExistentCustomerId = 99999


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### [Setup][Customers] Login as admin (session prerequisite)
POST {{AutoService_ApiService_HostAddress}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{AdminEmail}}",
  "password": "{{AdminPassword}}"
}

###

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  LIST CUSTOMERS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### [Positive][Customers] List all customers (200 expected)
GET {{AutoService_ApiService_HostAddress}}/api/customers

###

### [Setup][Customers] Logout admin, login as non-admin for auth check
POST {{AutoService_ApiService_HostAddress}}/api/auth/logout

###

### [Setup][Customers] Login as non-admin mechanic
POST {{AutoService_ApiService_HostAddress}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{NonAdminEmail}}",
  "password": "{{NonAdminPassword}}"
}

###

### [Positive][Customers] Non-admin can list customers (200 expected — read is authorized, not admin-only)
GET {{AutoService_ApiService_HostAddress}}/api/customers

###

### [Positive][Customers] Lookup customer by email for scheduler flow (200 expected)
# Expected success semantics:
# - 200 OK with scheduler lookup payload fields: id, firstName, middleName, lastName, email, phoneNumber, vehicles.
# - For real customer emails, email should be the normalized customer email and vehicles should list the customer's vehicles.
### [Case][Customers] GET /api/customers/by-email?email={{KnownCustomerEmail}}

GET {{AutoService_ApiService_HostAddress}}/api/customers/by-email?email={{KnownCustomerEmail}}

###

### [Positive][Customers] Lookup customer by email with casing/whitespace normalization (200 expected)
GET {{AutoService_ApiService_HostAddress}}/api/customers/by-email?email=%20{{KnownCustomerEmail}}%20

###

### [Positive][Customers] Lookup customer by mechanic email when linked customer may not exist yet (200 expected)
# Expected success semantics:
# - 200 OK (mechanic email is a valid scheduler lookup target).
# - If no linked customer exists yet, response resolves to mechanic identity (email={{NonAdminEmail}}) with empty vehicles.
# - If linked customer exists, response resolves to linked customer payload (typically mechanic-owner-{id}@customers.arsm.local) with linked vehicles.
### [Case][Customers] GET /api/customers/by-email?email={{NonAdminEmail}}

GET {{AutoService_ApiService_HostAddress}}/api/customers/by-email?email={{NonAdminEmail}}

###

### [Negative][Customers] Lookup customer by invalid email format (422 expected)
GET {{AutoService_ApiService_HostAddress}}/api/customers/by-email?email=not-an-email

###

### [Negative][Customers] Lookup customer by unknown email (404 expected)
GET {{AutoService_ApiService_HostAddress}}/api/customers/by-email?email=unknown.scheduler.lookup.{{RunId}}@example.test

###

### [Negative][Customers] Unauthenticated list customers (401 expected)
# NOTE: Run this after manually clearing cookies / in a fresh session.
# Uncomment to use:
# GET {{AutoService_ApiService_HostAddress}}/api/customers

###

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  GET CUSTOMER BY ID
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### [Setup][Customers] Login as admin for single-customer queries
POST {{AutoService_ApiService_HostAddress}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{AdminEmail}}",
  "password": "{{AdminPassword}}"
}

###

### [Positive][Customers] Get seeded customer by id (200 expected, includes vehicle list)
GET {{AutoService_ApiService_HostAddress}}/api/customers/{{SeedCustomerId}}

###

### [Negative][Customers] Get non-existent customer (404 expected)
GET {{AutoService_ApiService_HostAddress}}/api/customers/{{NonExistentCustomerId}}
